1-2 SPC setup, Week 3-12 continuous monitoring\n- Success Metric: Process Cpk ≥1.33; defect rate <2% by end of month 3\n\n2. Machine Calibration Preventive Program\n- Develop calibration maintenance schedule for Pai-32 (currently OEE 0.42, Quality 0.86)\n- Implement weekly color sensor calibration checks (vs. current reactive approach)\n- Create calibration baseline documentation for both machines\n- Assign: Maintenance Technician (1 FTE dedicated)\n- Resource: Calibration equipment, spare sensors, preventive maintenance software\n- Timeline: Week 1 baseline establishment, ongoing weekly checks\n- Success Metric: Pai-32 Quality metric improve from 0.86 to ≥0.95; calibration drift <0.3%\n\n3. Material Defect Investigation (2 defects)\n- Audit paint supplier quality records for batches used 2026-07-06\n- Implement incoming material inspection for paint viscosity and color consistency\n- Establish supplier SLA with defect rate limits\n- Assign: Quality Engineer + Procurement (1.5 FTE)\n- Resource: Material testing equipment, supplier audit capability\n- Success Metric: Material-related defects eliminated; supplier quality score ≥95%\n\n4. Design Issue Assessment (2 defects)\n- Review product design specifications for color matching requirements\n- Evaluate if design tolerances are achievable with current equipment capability\n- Recommend design modifications if Pai-31/Pai-32 capability insufficient\n- Assign: Design Engineer + Process Engineer (1.5 FTE)\n- Resource: Design review meetings, capability studies\n- Success Metric: Design-process alignment confirmed; design changes implemented if needed\n\nLONG-TERM ACTIONS (3-12 months):\n\n1. Machine Availability & OEE Improvement (Pai-32: Availability 0.72)\n- Conduct root cause analysis on Pai-32 availability loss (28% downtime)\n- Evaluate equipment upgrade or replacement feasibility\n- Implement predictive maintenance using sensor data from maintenance events\n- Assign: Maintenance Manager + Equipment Engineer (2 FTE)\n- Resource: Predictive maintenance software, equipment diagnostics, capital budget\n- Timeline: Month 3-4 analysis, Month 5-12 implementation\n- Success Metric: Pai-32 Availability improve from 0.72 to ≥0.90; OEE from 0.42 to ≥0.65\n\n2. Automated Color Verification System\n- Evaluate inline color measurement system (spectrophotometer) for real-time defect detection\n- Implement automated quality gates before product release from Paint work center\n- Integrate with MES for automatic defect flagging and traceability\n- Assign: Automation Engineer + Quality Engineer (2 FTE)\n- Resource: Inline measurement equipment, MES integration, installation labor\n- Timeline: Month 4-6 evaluation, Month 7-12 implementation\n- Success Metric: 100% color defect detection rate; defect escape rate <0.1%\n\n3. Maintenance-Quality Integration Framework\n- Develop formal procedure linking maintenance activities to quality monitoring\n- Create maintenance impact assessment for all future Setup/Changeover and Software Updates\n- Establish cross-functional maintenance-quality review meetings (bi-weekly)\n- Assign: Maintenance Manager + Quality Manager (1 FTE)\n- Resource: Process documentation, meeting facilitation\n- Success Metric: Zero unplanned quality impacts from maintenance; 100% maintenance pre-approval\n\nRESOURCE SUMMARY:\n- Immediate: 3.5 FTE, $15K equipment\n- Short-term: 7 FTE, $45K equipment/software\n- Long-term: 4 FTE, $120K capital equipment\n- Total 12-month investment: 14.5 FTE, $180K\n\nKEY SUCCESS METRICS (Overall):\n- Color mismatch defects: 13 → 0 within 90 days\n- Pai-32 OEE: 0.42 → 0.65 within 12 months\n- Pai-32 Availability: 0.72 → 0.90 within 12 months\n- Process Cpk: Establish baseline → ≥1.33 within 90 days\n- Maintenance-induced defects: Eliminate within 30 days', 'priority_level': 'High'}}> | streaming
