2026-07-13 15:12:05,357 - strands.tools.executors._executor - DEBUG - tool_use=<{'toolUseId': 'toolu_01FrSpzvGYtPwvB4DgCK9TL3', 'name': 'send_email_notification', 'input': {'subject': 'URGENT: Color Mismatch Defect Analysis & Immediate Action Plan - Paint & Finish Work Center', 'message': 'EXECUTIVE SUMMARY\n13 Color Mismatch defects detected in Paint & Finish work center (Pai-31, Pai-32) on 2026-07-06. Root cause analysis confirms process variation, machine calibration drift, and maintenance correlation with Setup/Changeover and Software Updates (11:26-13:34 hours). Machine Pai-32 operating at critical OEE 0.42 with Quality score 0.86 and Availability 0.72. Immediate intervention required to prevent quality escalation and production loss.\n\nKEY FINDINGS\n• 13 Color Mismatch defects in Paint & Finish work center (Pai-31, Pai-32) on 2026-07-06 [source: Maintenance Correlation Analysis]\n• Root causes: Process Variation (4 instances), Machine Calibration (3 instances), Material Defect (2), Operator Error (2), Design Issue (2) [source: Root Cause Analysis]\n• Machine Pai-32 OEE degraded to 0.42 with Quality 0.86 and Availability 0.72 [source: OEE Metrics]\n• Maintenance correlation confirmed: Setup/Changeover and Software Updates during 11:26-13:34 hours triggered defect spike [source: Maintenance Correlation Analysis]\n• Validation status PENDING_HUMAN_REVIEW with 0.85 confidence [source: Analysis Validation]\n\nSUPPORTING DATA\n| Metric | Machine Pai-31 | Machine Pai-32 | Impact |\n|--------|---|---|---|\n| Defect Count | 6 | 7 | Quality Risk |\n| OEE Score | not available in data | 0.42 | Critical |\n| Quality Score | not available in data | 0.86 | Degraded |\n| Availability | not available in data | 0.72 | Below Target |\n| Root Cause: Calibration | 2 | 1 | Immediate Fix |\n| Root Cause: Process Variation | 2 | 2 | Process Control |\n\nIMMEDIATE ACTION PLAN (0-7 Days)\nOWNERSHIP: Equipment Engineering + Paint & Finish Supervisor\n1. Emergency Machine Calibration Recovery (Pai-32 priority): Recalibrate color spray nozzles, pressure regulators, and spray pattern sensors. Target completion: 48 hours. Risk if delayed: Continued defect generation, customer quality escapes.\n2. Maintenance Event Documentation: Complete root cause documentation for Setup/Changeover and Software Updates events (11:26-13:34 window). Identify software parameter changes affecting color consistency. Timeline: 7 days.\n\nSHORT-TERM ACTIONS (7-14 Days)\nOWNERSHIP: Paint & Finish Work Center + Quality Engineering\n• Process Variation Control: Implement tighter spray pressure monitoring (±2 PSI tolerance). Validate with 50-unit trial run.\n• Material Defect Investigation: Audit incoming paint batch (2026-07-06) for viscosity and pigment consistency. Coordinate with Procurement.\n• Operator Error Mitigation: Conduct refresher training on color calibration procedures for operators assigned to Pai-31/Pai-32. Certification required before resuming production.\n\nLONG-TERM ACTIONS (14+ Days)\nOWNERSHIP: Manufacturing Engineering + Maintenance\n• Design Issue Resolution: Evaluate spray gun design for Pai-32 (7 defects vs 6 on Pai-31). Consider equipment upgrade or design modification.\n• Preventive Maintenance Enhancement: Establish monthly calibration schedule for color spray systems. Integrate software update validation into changeover procedures.\n• OEE Improvement Target: Restore Pai-32 OEE from 0.42 to >0.75 within 30 days through combined calibration, process control, and maintenance optimization.\n\nIMPACT SUMMARY\nQuality: Eliminate color mismatch defects to prevent customer returns and warranty claims. Cost: Reduce scrap and rework from defect generation. Safety: Ensure proper equipment calibration prevents operator exposure to pressure anomalies. Efficiency: Restore Pai-32 availability from 0.72 to >0.85 and OEE to target levels.\n\nCRITICAL RISKS IF NOT ADDRESSED\n• Continued defect generation leading to customer quality escapes and potential order cancellation\n• Machine Pai-32 availability further degradation impacting production schedule\n• Operator safety risk from uncalibrated spray pressure systems\n\nDETAILED REPORT ATTACHED\nFull analysis with maintenance correlation data, root cause breakdown, and validation details available at: https://dfmw0zqekwl4n.cloudfront.net/proxy/8501/pdf=MES_Analysis_Report_20260713_151118.pdf?pdf=MES_Analysis_Report_20260713_151118.pdf\n\nNEXT STEPS\n1. Approve Emergency Machine Calibration Recovery (Pai-32) within 24 hours\n2. Assign Equipment Engineering lead for calibration execution\n3. Schedule Paint & Finish supervisor briefing on action plan and timeline\n4. Confirm Maintenance team availability for documentation and preventive measures\n\nValidation Status: PENDING_HUMAN_REVIEW (0.85 confidence). Recommend immediate human review and approval before full production resumption on affected machines.', 'pdf_filename': 'MES_Analysis_Report_20260713_151118.pdf', 'priority': 'High'}}> | streaming
